From 19b21ace1187ead773ea1e0b1a83c6b7298affca Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 15:00:03 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] rsx: Add built-in RSX3D compatibility shim

Purpose:

Tex Murphy: Overseer requires Intel RSX 3D for its startup probing and in-game voice playback. The original redistributable is proprietary and external wrappers only work around parts of the behavior, so add a built-in rsx.dll implementation instead.

Development:

The implementation was developed by comparing Wine traces against the native RSX3D runtime, collecting focused RSX method logs, and dumping waveOut buffers from both native RSX3D and Wine. Those captures showed that the game configures RSX for wave output, streams voice buffers through RSX emitter/listener style COM objects, and expects SQSH/WAVE voice assets to be decoded into 22050 Hz mono PCM before submission to waveOut.

Keep the waveOut dump hook guarded behind WINE_DUMP_WAVEOUT=1, with WINE_DUMP_WAVEOUT_DIR selecting the output directory, so the native-vs-Wine PCM comparison can be reproduced without affecting normal playback.

Function:

- Register the RSX COM classes and install the Intel Realistic Sound Experience registry key with Device Type set to wave so games do not show the missing RSX3D warning dialog.

- Provide the exported entry points and class factory plumbing needed by applications that probe CreateRSX, DllGetClassObject, and the RSX listener/emitter CLSIDs.

- For playback, queue RIFF/WAVE buffers through winmm waveOut, keep enough shared state to emulate RSX stream completion, and support the stream-ring/source refill patterns observed from the original DLL.

- The SQSH decoder handles the game's block format directly; the final fix came from comparing native waveOut dumps against our decoded output and correcting the special-command bit reader so it reads the 2-bit SQSH control command instead of reusing the previous sample width.

This allows Overseer to run without installing native rsx.dll/aaudio.dll, removes the RSX warning popup, and restores in-game voice line playback.
